edu.umass.cs.nio

Class IOSSSLDataProcessingWorker

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.nio.IOSSSLDataProcessingWorker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataProcessingWorker, InterfaceMessageExtractor

    public class IOSSSLDataProcessingWorker
extends java.lang.Object
implements InterfaceMessageExtractor
    Author:
    arun This class does SSL wrap/unwrap functions respectively right before NIO performs an (unencrypted) outgoing network write and right after NIO receives (encrypted) incoming network reads. It is really not a "message extractor", just an InterfaceDataProcessingWorker + wrap functionality, but it implements InterfaceMessageExtractor so that it is easy for MessageNIOTransport to conduct its functions without worrying about whether NIOTransport.worker is InterfaceMessageExtractor or not. Nevertheless, this class can be used simply with NIOTransport for secure byte stream communication as InterfaceMessageExtractor is also an InterfaceDataProcessingWorker.
